From 67f22306caf69c75cd4b019a389e58fe17034678 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 05:52:40 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 003/174] PGCL: fix PAGE_CACHE/vm_pgoff unit mismatch across
 mm/ subsystems

Fix pervasive unit confusion between MMUPAGE-unit (vm_pgoff, linear_page_index)
and PAGE-unit (page cache folio->index, xarray index) in 11 files.

Key fixes:
- Anon folio->index now stored in PAGE-unit via pgoff_mmu_to_page() conversion
  in rmap.c __folio_add_new_anon_rmap, matching file-backed folio convention.
  All comparisons against folio->index updated (ksm.c, rmap.c assertion).

- Page cache lookups (xarray, filemap_lock_folio, shmem_get_folio) now receive
  PAGE-unit indices via pgoff_mmu_to_page() conversion (madvise.c, khugepaged.c,
  userfaultfd.c, shmem.c, mincore.c, migrate.c).

- PTE walker address-to-pgoff conversions use MMUPAGE_SHIFT instead of PAGE_SHIFT
  (mapping_dirty_helpers.c, nommu.c). TLB flush ranges use MMUPAGE_SIZE.

- mmap pgoff-to-bytes conversions use MMUPAGE_SHIFT (huge_memory.c thp_get_unmapped_area,
  shmem.c shmem_get_unmapped_area, nommu.c region sharing and remap_vmalloc_range).

- File size comparisons use MMUPAGE_SIZE denominator to match MMUPAGE-unit pgoff
  (userfaultfd.c mcopy_atomic_pte bounds check).

Tested: PAGE_MMUSHIFT=0 and PAGE_MMUSHIFT=2 both boot with 8/8 comprehensive
tests passing. No kernel BUGs, no bad page maps, no RSS counter errors.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
